<br>
I am wondering why the spell damage nerf still exists on EverQuest pvp servers. <br>
<br>
The nerf was enacted in late 1999, long before Kunark and Velious came out. The reason for the spell damage nerf, supposedly, was that Spells were designed for PvE encounters, thus making them too powerful in PvP. A lot has changed since then. <br>
<br>
Kunark and Velious made Melee characters and Hybrids incredibly more powerful. Further, the Level of Resists has seen a phenomenal increase with the introduction of Blue Diamond gear, velium jewelery, and the incredibly powerful new items that drop throughout Kunark, Velious and the revised Planar drops. <br>
<br>
If spell damage was nerfed because it was designed for PvE, why aren't Resists nerfed in accord with that same theory? It it common for high level players (40-60) on PvP servers to have Resists in the 150-200 range. <br>
<br>
I am a level 52 wizard on the Sullon Zek server. Setting aside for a moment the recent PvP resist nerf disaster, the level of resists on the server are already phenomenal. Velious offerse several easy gem quests, and many of my opponents are already wearing full diamond and blue diamond resist gear. <br>
<br>
Root in PvP is a joke. At level 50+, fighting anyone in range or red, Root spells will land about 1 in 500 times. Snare spells (Bonds of Force) are likewise useless. Stun spells (Clash's) are similarly a waste of mana. Now, on top of all of that, Since the wizard is the only pure damage caster without a DoT, a Pet or a Resistance Debuff, the non-lure damage spells are very often doing less than 1:1 Damage:Mana ratio. <br>
<br>
For example, the level 51 wizard nuke, Draught of Fire, Is supposed to do 650+ in PvE for 215 Mana. In PvP, it does a maximum of about 407 damage for 215 mana. Many many many of the Even Con and High Green opponents I fight regularly resist the spell to the tun of taking 51-200 damage. It almost never hits for full. <br>
<br>
Is that really Verant's vision for PvP wizards? Instead of the gods of DD, we are the laughing stock. Not only do our spells get resists often, but we have no Debuff. <br>
<br>
Now, a 51 druid casting their level 49 fire based nuke, accompanied by their massive Fire debuff, can regularly outdamage our level 51 fire nuke. <br>
<br>
At high level pvp, as a wizard with 2.5 years of pvp experience, there is very little I cast besides Lures and Shock of Lightning. <br>
<br>
Are my Roots supposed to be worthless? <br>
Are my snares not supposed to ever land? <br>
Are my Clash spells supposed to be a waste? <br>
Are my non-lure nukes supposed to be doing 10-30 percent of their PvE max for 100percent of the mana cost? <br>
<br>
<br>
Beyond the obvious fact that Resists are completely out of control, and that wizards are the MOST dd dependent and LEAST able to debuff, why on earth is their still a spell damge nerf? <br>
<br>
<br>
Pet HP wasnt nerfed. <br>
Melee AC/HP/ATK/DEF wasnt nerfed. <br>
Heal Spells were not nerfed. <br>
<br>
It seems to me that the useful life of the spell damage nerf has expired. <br>
<br>
Please consider making PvP fair again by eliminating the spell damage nerf. Additionally, a Resist Cap of 120 in any category would likewise be appropriate in making EQ PvP fair. <br>
<br>
Finally, if you are not going to remove the spell damage cap, then please at least be decent enough to similarly nerf the mana cost of the spell. Not only have you knee-capped the Damage per Spell, but the total damage output in a bar of mana by not reducing mana cost on the spells. <br>
<br>
If you wont do any of that, how about making the wizard staff of temperate flux a meaningful debuff tool? It currently reduces FIRE and COLD by SIX, 6. (That is not a typo, 6). What about 60? Or at least 45? Shouldnt the most mana-dependent, DD dependent caster be able to debuff? <br>
<br>
Thanks for your time. <br>
<br>
Mezmoriah <br>
Level 52 DE Wizard of Sullon Zek <br>
<br>
<br>
