</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/uvachir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vachir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tavern Regular</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/22/01 10:38:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My comment to Verant re Spell Damage Nerf &amp; PvP Resi</span><hr size=1> I think wizards are underpowered in pvp due to the damage nerf, other classes that have damage sources besides DD arn't as bad off but wizards only offense is their spells.  I've heard way too many times that melees in general can easily defeat casters at 50+, obviously this was not the case when the nerf was implemented and since things have changed a lot since then the balance is now toward the melee side while casters are somewhat underpowered against them.  <br>
<br>
As to what this would do to pure caster battles, it would probably make things more of who got the first spell off, but it's pretty much like that now, I don't think casters in general would complain about gaining more power to their spells as it wouldn't change the balance much between the different casters (except for maybe giving wizards more of the edge they need), and it would be very benificial against melees. <p>--------------------<BR>
<B>Vachir</B>, Dark Elf Shadowknight<BR>
